What the Atlas fork adds on top of OpenJarvis:

  - A full-duplex local voice loop (barge-in, wake word, speaker
    identification with owner/family/guest trust tiers) built on Pipecat,
    with local STT/LLM/TTS by default (faster-whisper, Ollama, Kokoro) —
    no API keys and no per-minute cost required.
  - A tool layer the voice loop drives directly: calendar (native Google
    OAuth), email triage, reminders with nag/acknowledge loops, SMS,
    invoices, notes, news, weather, knowledge/wiki memory, vision.
  - An agent hub: work is delegated to registered specialist agents over
    an A2A fabric with mid-task talk-back, blocking questions, and a
    human approval gate for sensitive actions.
  - Remote surfaces: a phone voice loop (WebRTC), a Wear OS watch client
    (the atlas-watch repository), an approvals API with per-device
    credentials, and a smart-glasses bridge (MentraOS).
  - A proactive initiative engine: scheduled and event-driven surfacing
    (morning brief, calendar lead-ins, follow-ups) with quiet hours and
    silence mode.
